President Obama met with former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg to discuss ways to address gun violence in America. They talked about keeping guns away from those who shouldn't have access to them and discussed potential actions at the state and local level. The President also thanked Bloomberg for his commitment to this issue. They also discussed the importance of state and local climate action in implementing the historic climate agreement reached in Paris, with Bloomberg's role as UN Special Envoy for Cities and Climate being highlighted. Senior Advisor Valerie Jarrett was also present at the meeting.